===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈʧɛkmeɪt/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"tSEkmeIt/}}

===Etymology===
From [[Persian]] šāh māt, ''the king is dead'' or ''the king is helpless'' (borrowed through Middle English [[chekmat]], through Old French [[eschec mat]]).

===Interjection===
'''checkmate'''

# {{chess}} Word called out by the [[victor]] when making the conclusive move.
# {{literally}} The king is dead.

